global_flags.description: Recognize .EQ and .EN even when followed by a character other than space or newline.
Prohibit newlines within delimiters.  This option allows eqn to recover better from missing closing delimiters.

output for the device dev.  In most cases, the effect of this is to define a macro dev with a value of 1; eqnrc uses this to provide definitions appropriate for the device.  However, if the specified driver is “MathML”, the output  is  MathML  markup  rather than troff input, and eqnrc is not loaded at all.  The default output device is ps.
Specify  delimiters x for left and y for right ends of equations not bracketed by .EQ/.EN.  x and y need not be distinct.  Any “delim xy” statements in the source file override this option.
Set sub- and superscripts n points smaller than the surrounding text.  This option is deprecated.  eqn normally sets sub- and  super‐ scripts at 70% of the type size of the surrounding text.
Reduce the type size of subscripts at most once relative to the base type size for the equation.
is equivalent to “gsize n”.  This option is deprecated.
